{"title":"fix: Update vigil-app Deployment with valid nginx image tag","body":"Root cause: Deployment manifest declares invalid image tag 'nginx:bad-tag-v9' which does not exist in Docker registry.

Evidence: Failed to pull image "nginx:bad-tag-v9": rpc error: code = NotFound desc = failed to pull and unpack image "docker.io/library/nginx:bad-tag-v9": failed to resolve reference "docker.io/library/nginx:bad-tag-v9": docker.io/library/nginx:bad-tag-v9: not found

This fix updates the image tag to 'nginx:latest' to resolve the image pull failure."}
